1.jpg','46603102687e798dcbeomr3.jpg','Escape the hustle and bustle of the city with unsurpassed leisure facilities in a scenic ambience.\r\n\r\nLe Revive is our authentic Ayurvedic spa offering a variety of services to refresh the mind and mend the body. The 5,000-year-old healing system of Ayurveda is a holistic, natural therapy that aims to restore the wellbeing of the individual through a series of personalized treatments and medicines.\r\n\r\nAn experience at the spa leaves you feeling rested and refreshed. Close your eyes, relax, take a deep breath, and feel the tension eased away as gentle hands rub oils deep into your pores. Feel your muscles open up to the experienced touch as your mind ascends into a state best described as Nirvana.\r\n\r\nThe fitness centre on the top floor has a breathtaking view of the backwaters. Our qualified instructors plan customized fitness programs for different clientele. The state-of-the-art gym is equipped with a steam room and sauna.\r\n\r\nPeaceful, quiet, and serene would best describe our Yoga Centre. Starting with a hymn in sync with the time of day, the yoga instructor takes you on a journey of discovery. Meditation and specific exercises ensure complete relaxation and rejuvenation.\r\n\r\nThe three-tier outdoor swimming pool has a separate whirlpool, Jacuzzi, and children’s pool. Also available are outdoor sports facilities such as a jogging track, water sports, sunset cruises, and fishing.\r\n\r\nIndulge on the backwaters in a Kettuvalam (traditional Kerala house boat). As you lie back and look at the blue skies, the silent calm of the backwaters and greenery makes life come to a standstill amongst the surreal beauty surrounding you. The houseboats can be booked for day cruises and overnight stays.\r\n\r\nThe art gallery, 24-hour library, 24-hour business centre, 24-hour travel desk, and beauty salon are all perfect for a moment of leisure.','Le Meridien Cochin Tower Suites  Ernakulam, Maradu Cochin, Kerala682304',55,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','Cochin\r\nHotel & Convention Centre situated in 18 acres of land with close access to city centre, amidst backwaters. Proximity to Infopark, business & industrial hub and popular tourist locations in the city.','le-meridian--2','2013-07-20 16:40:21','2013-07-20 16:40:21',NULL,NULL),(175,'Vivanta by Taj','1161636305.jpg','thumb_Vivanta-Malabar-web-1.jpg','017.jpg','45dsc_0115.jpg','Vivanta by Taj - Malabar, Kerala entices guests to explore the nuances of the finest Indian and international cuisines, serving traditional and contemporary favourites. The atmosphere is lively. The crowd exceptional. Jet set culinarians sample different exotic menus night after night. Pepper the multi cuisine all-day diner with delightful views of the backwaters and lush gardens. The Rice Boat is a fresh take on speciality sea food with an accent on local Kerala cuisine. Fine dining it is. The Thai Pavilion proudly holds sway as Kerala\'s only authentic Thai restaurant. Dolphin\'s Point is spot on for its bay side location serving outstanding barbeque and grills in season. And everyone gravitates to Mattancherry Bar for a heady evening with lots of spirit and character.','Vivanta by Taj - Malabar, CochinHotels in Kochi Near Airport (COK), Tagore Rd, Thopumpady, Kochi, Kerala 682009',55,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','35','vivanta-by-taj--2','2013-07-20 16:42:36','2013-07-20 16:42:36',NULL,NULL),(176,'The Oberoi Udaivilas','PG_UDA_006__1_.jpg','PG_UDA_009.jpg','PG_UDA_012.jpg','PG_UDA_018.jpg','Udaipur, in the heart of Rajasthan, is a city of majestic palaces and beautiful lakes. Here, adorning the banks of Lake Pichola and standing witness to the historic City Palace, The Oberoi Udaivilas captures all the romance and splendour of a royal era.\r\n\r\nConceived as a traditional Indian palace, The Oberoi Udaivilas showcases the rich heritage of the Mewar region of Rajasthan with its rambling courtyards, gentle rippling fountains, reflection pools and verdant gardens. Grand architecture inspired by the palaces of Rajasthan present a picture of majesty resplendent with pavilions and domes that lead you to a journey of discovery. Interiors embellished with decorative domes, hand painted frescoes, intricate mirror work and beautifully crafted artefacts create an ambience of regal splendour.','Udaipur - 313001, ',10,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','Udaipur - 313001, ','the-oberoi-udaivilas--2','2013-07-20 16:48:58','2013-07-20 16:48:58',NULL,NULL),(177,'The Ravla Khempur','SNF30T02SE-_1538664a.jpg','Ravla_Khempur__Khempur_village__Rajasthan1.jpg','horse_safari9.GIF','734728_533435320012562_1474634568_n.jpg','The Ravla Khempur has a passionate history of true Mewari valour that dates back to 1628 AD. An enemy, in order to avenge the killing of his brother, plotted to assassinate the young Prince Jagat Singh of Mewar. His plans were over-heard by Khemraj Dadhivadia whilst he was having his sword sharpened in the market place. Khemraj didn’t utter a word of what he had heard to anyone and left quietly. On the fateful day when the young prince was out hunting, the would-be assassin charged up towards him, intent on murder. When the deadly blade of the enemy’s sword was inches away from the prince, Khemraj leapt out from nowhere, and with a single stroke of his sword, beheaded the attacker. To honour this gallant act, Mewar’s grateful Maharana rewarded Khemraj Dadhivadia with a village and named it Khempur.\r\nThe title ‘Ravla’ in Rajasthan refers to the home of a village chieftain”. In earlier days, the Ravla was the focal point of the entire village. Functions such as village welfare, collection of taxes, administration of law and order, and the initiation of festivals took place in the Ravla. Ravla Khempur exudes historical ambience and is graced with breathtaking surroundings. The lofty terraces, open courtyards, sprawling gardens, domes, arches and canopied balconies transport one back in time. Khempur village developed over the centuries to one side of the Ravla. It comprises a small, random and attractive cluster of typical rural dwellings and shops, and shaded squares where the villagers discuss the affairs of the world or share the local gossip. For the visitor, this is a side of India that has its own fascination; the cheerful welcome and natural hospitality of the village folk who ask nothing more than to enjoy a chat over a cup of tea. Beyond the village is an expanse of verdant farmland stretching off towards distant mountains: not a single blot on the landscape to spoil this serenely beautiful panorama.',' Village & Post: Khempur, Via: Mavli-313203,      District: Udaipur,       Rajasthan, INDIA',10,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout',' Village & Post: Khempur, Via: Mavli-313203,\r\n     District: Udaipur, \r\n     Rajasthan, INDIA','the-ravla-khempur--2','2013-07-20 16:50:57','2013-07-20 16:50:57',NULL,NULL),(178,'Taj Lake Palace ','Taj-Lake-Palace1.jpg','lake-palace-udaipur-b3.jpg','IMG_5145.JPG','4248052142_fd80a972ca_z.jpg','Yes, much of the resplendence of the Lake Palace Hotel has to do with the sheer fact that it is seemingly floating on Pichola Lake. But with open-air courtyards, marble swimming pool and magnificent terraces, it is also one classy (and deservedly famous) palace unto itself.\r\n\r\nIt\'s no wonder this shining 250-year-old structure has seen many a white wedding dress flowing along its magical main terrace, which has an extraordinary view and sits above a lotus pond. When you\'ve maxed out your tolerance for outrageously incredible views, come back down to earth with a chess game in the lounge, a brewskie in the bar or a session with the astrologer near the lobby. Or you could just luxuriate in your room - which just might be enlivened with silks, artefacts, ornate furnishings and intricate paintings or murals, and will certainly be equipped with mod cons. Some rooms are handsome, others are sumptuous. Any drawbacks? The restaurant here has received consistently mixed reviews from guests. And, when drought hits and the lake waters are low, the setting loses much of its majesty.','Lake Pichola, Udaipur, Rajasthan, 313001',10,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','Lake Pichola, Udaipur, Rajasthan, 313001','taj-lake-palace--2','2013-07-20 16:52:33','2013-07-20 16:52:33',NULL,NULL),(179,'The Leela Palace','leela-palace-udaipur-sishe_mahal_long.jpg','arrival-by-boat-The-Leela-Palace-Udaipur-Rajasthan-Nexus-Travel-Solutions-Luxury-Bespoke-Holidays-India1.jpg','cn_image_1.size.leela-palace-kempinski-udaipur-udaipur-rajasthan-india-108673-3.jpg','leela-palace-udaipur-india-ampersand-travel-6.jpg','With a majestic location on the Lake Pichola and spectacular view of the Aravalli Mountains, The Leela Palace evokes grandeur and opulence of the land of the Mewar. Beautifully designed to reflect the surrounding style and influences, the intricate craftsmanship and world-class amenities designed by Jeffrey A. Wilkes, while part of Lim Teo Wilkes Design Works, and the attention to detail in the art and embellishment by Mrs. Madhu Nair makes it an ultimate palace experience and regal indulgence.\r\n',' Lake Pichola, Udaipur 313001 ',10,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','With a majestic location on the Lake Pichola and spectacular view of the Aravalli Mountains, The Leela Palace evokes grandeur and opulence of the land of the Mewar. Beautifully designed to reflect the surrounding style and influences, the intricate craftsmanship and world-class amenities designed by Jeffrey A. Wilkes, while part of Lim Teo Wilkes Design Works, and the attention to detail in the art and embellishment by Mrs. Madhu Nair makes it an ultimate palace experience and regal indulgence.\r\n','the-leela-palace--2','2013-07-20 16:54:56','2013-07-20 16:54:56',NULL,NULL),(180,'Fateh Garh','01_thezenanamahal_thecity_palacecomplex_udaipur.jpg','fg9.jpg','DSC_3093.JPG','DSC_3084.JPG','Hotel Fateh Garh belongs to the Heritage Renaissance School of building. Heritage Renaissance - a term used to describe th