al classicism with gilded art deco, houses an impressive collection of 17th- and 18th-century paintings, and has hosted everyone from princesses to pop stars. The high-ceilinged rooms have it all, from French linen and puffy pillows to marble baths and finely-crafted furniture. The Spice Route restaurant has real wow-factor – with a wooden temple-style interior – though the Thai food isn’t quite as stunning.\r\nThe Imperial is a legend that offers a unique experience embracing facets of India\'s history, and stands witness to the birth of the capital city of New Delhi. Built in 1931 by Blomfield; one of Sir Edwin Lutyen’s associates and inaugurated by Lord Willingdon in 1936, the Hotel is known for its contemporary colonial style. As New Delhi’s landmark Hotel, it is located on Janpath, the erstwhile Queensway, steps away from the renowned shopping district and major attractions of the city.','Janpath Lane, Connaught Place, New Delhi,Delhi 110001',15,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','Janpath Lane, Connaught Place, New Delhi,Delhi 110001','the-imperial-new-delhi--2','2013-07-20 18:16:44','2013-07-20 18:16:44',NULL,NULL),(182,'Hyatt Regency New Delhi','hyatt-regency-hotel-delhi-10.jpg','hyatt-regency-hotel-delhi-7.jpg','hyatt-regency-hotel-delhi-5.jpg','hyatt-regency-newdelhi-india-1.jpg','Hyatt Regency Delhi, one of the best luxury hotels in New Delhi provides a wide range of services guaranteed to satisfy the needs of the most discerning guests. Our business hotel offers unparalleled guest services, including transportation, event venue hire, boutique shopping, multilingual staff, Business Centre featuring 24-hour secretarial services and wedding planning. Hyatt Regency New Delhi luxury hotels is Conveniently located in the commercial hub of the city, near the international airport, Hyatt Regency Delhi is strategically placed to cater to your guest service requirements, ensuring that your stay is unforgettable.','Bhikaji Cama Place, Ring Road, New Delhi, India 110607',15,