al Airport (DEL).','Le Méridien New Delhi Windsor PlaceNew Delhi, New DelhiIndia',15,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout',' 8,Windsor Place, Janpath, New Delhi, Delhi 110001','le-meridien-new-delhi--3','2013-07-20 18:22:30','2013-07-20 18:22:30',NULL,NULL),(187,'The Oberoi, New Delhi','PG_DEL_004.jpg','tondOverview_01.jpg','tondOverviewL_02.jpg','tondOverviewL_03.jpg','The hotel reflects the capital city’s spirit in a harmonious blend of tradition and contemporary sophistication. Recognised as a pioneer amongst luxury hotels in India, The Oberoi, New Delhi was the first hotel to offer a 24 hour personal Butler service. Its exquisite interiors, impeccable service and fine cuisine combine to make it amongst the most graceful and elegant downtown hotels in Delhi.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Opposite Delhi public School, Dr Zakir Hussain Marg, New Delhi, DL 110003',15,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','Opposite Delhi public School, Dr Zakir Hussain Marg, New Delhi, DL 110003','the-oberoi-new-delhi--2','2013-07-20 18:23:56','2013-07-20 18:23:56',NULL,NULL),(188,'The Grand, New Delhi','business-header.jpg','spa-header.jpg','accommodation-header.jpg','experiance_the_grand_banner.jpg','The Grand, New Delhi a five star luxury hotel located in the heart of city, welcomes its guest to experience an artful balance of contemporary elegance and modern design\r\nThis Luxury Hotel is newly refurbished throughout from the splendid white lobby, newly appointed rooms, purifying spa experience, a signature blend of restaurants, bar and lounge along with impeccable service, we are further geared to recognize the distinctiveness of luxury travellers.',' Nelson Mandela Road, Vasant Kunj Phase II, New Delhi -110070 New Delhi, Delhi',15,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout',' Nelson Mandela Road, Vasant Kunj Phase II, New Delhi -110070 New Delhi, Delhi','the-grand-new-delhi','2013-07-20 18:25:50','2013-07-20 18:25:50',NULL,NULL),(189,'Trident Hotel, Delhi','trident_gurgaon__1_.jpg','trident_gurgaon_entrance.jpg','Deluxe_Garden_View_Room_2.jpg','trident_gurgaon_Executive_Suite.jpg','The award winning Trident, Gurgaon, is set amongst 7 acres of landscaped gardens, walkways, courtyards, reflection pools and fountains. The hotel is located in the central business district of Gurgaon, a part of the New Delhi National Capital Region. Its resort like ambience includes 129 rooms, 6 executive suites and a presidential suite.\r\n\r\nTrident, Gurgaon has been voted \'Asia\'s Leading Hotel\' at the World Travel Awards, 2012.\r\nSurrounded by landscaped gardens, walkways, courtyards, reflection pools and fountains, the Trident, Gurgaon\'s 129 rooms and 7 suites are located in the hotel’s imposing yet serene edifice.','Plot No. 443, Shankar Chowk, Udyog Vihar Phase V, Gurgaon, Haryana, 122016',15,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','Plot No. 443, Shankar Chowk, Udyog Vihar Phase V, Gurgaon, Haryana, 122016','trident-hotel-delhi--2','2013-07-20 18:27:44','2013-07-20 18:27:44',NULL,NULL),(190,'The Elgin Silver Oaks Hotel, Kalimpong','kalim-garden2.jpg','kalim-bedroom.jpg','the-elgin-silver-oaks.jpg','4013920_5_b.jpg','The Elgin Silver Oaks Kalimpong, was the home of a famous Jute magnate. It is now converted into a luxury Elgin boutique hotel in the Himalayas.\r\n\r\nLounging in the landscaped gardens in a profusion of colors, one is treated to breath-taking view at the Silver Oaks, Kalimpong. The natural décor is characteristic in the imposing Kanchenjunga which can be seen on a clear day, blooming petunias and asters, the serrated violet edges of iris, iridescent butterflies flitting through colourful azaleas, drooping geraniums, proud orchids and heaven, temporarily descends on earth. Sitting in one of the quaint gazebos, the tea seems to be flavoured by the refreshing winds of the Himalayas. The Silver Oaks was built in 1930 and once belonged to the prominent architect Frederick Desraj who built the old Teesta Bridge.\r\n\r\nA mesmerizing vision of rich hues and shades in glorious asters and petunias with colourful butterflies straddling the open air awaits you, as you step into the garden or the little gazebo to take a sip of the finest Darjeeling tea. The ground floor of the house was built in 1930 by a British jute magnate, who later sold the house to Fredrick Deshraj, an architect and builder, who also built the Teesta bridge.\r\n\r\nThe house was then bought by Mr. Diamond Oberoi in the early 1980\'s from Fredrick Deshraj. Mr. Oberoi added an extra floor as a natural extension of this style of architecture with added windows, allowing a better assortment of lights filling in the indoors and hallways. The Elgin Silver Oaks is now a luxury boutique hotel and provides the best luxury and comfort by integrating modern amenities tastefully with its heritage décor.\r\n\r\nThis residence is also decked with lithographs of old masters, period furniture, bookshelves with handpicked publications and a bar to ease the spirits and help relax. The soft tunes of the piano and the aroma of the food stir up a languor that is perfectly acquainted with a sedentary holiday mood.','	Rinking Pong Road  Kalimpong, WB 734301',50,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','	Rinking Pong Road  Kalimpong, WB 734301','the-elgin-silver-oaks-hotel-kalimpong--2','2013-07-20 18:32:32','2013-07-20 18:32:32',NULL,NULL),(191,'The Manu Maharani','th_07.jpg','th_10.jpg','th_11.jpg','th_06.jpg','The Manu Maharani\'s restaurant serves light fare, appetizers, and drinks. The hotel also has a snack bar/deli and a coffee shop/café. A bar/lounge is open for drinks. Room service is available 24 hours a day. The hotel serves a complimentary buffet breakfast each morning in the coffee shop. Recreational amenities include a health club, a sauna, a steam room, and a children\'s club. The property\'s full-service health spa has body treatments, facials, and beauty services. This 4-star property has a business center and offers a meeting/conference room, secretarial services, and audiovisual equipment. Wireless Internet access (surcharge) is available in public areas. This Nainital property has 101 square meters of event space consisting of a conference center and banquet facilities. Business services, wedding services, and tour/ticket assistance are available. Complimentary guest parking is limited, and available on a first-come, first-served basis. Additional property amenities include a terrace, barbecue grills, and an arcade/game room.','The Manu MaharaniGrassmere Estate, Near High Court, Mallital, Nainital, Uttarakhand 263001',42,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','The Manu Maharani','the-manu-maharani--2','2013-07-20 18:36:18','2013-07-20 18:36:18',NULL,NULL),(192,'The Naini Retreat','2nd.jpg','manu-4.jpg','manu-2.jpg','manu-5.jpg','Historically referred to as the residence of the Maharaja of Pilibhit, The Naini Retreat is one of the most prestigious of the heritage hotels in Nainital. This palatial building not only exudes an old world charm but also imbibes every imaginable marks of modern luxury. Tasteful bedrooms, an intimate dining room overlooking the valley, lush landscapes, a huge conference hall and a view of the Himalayas contribute to the creation of a fascinating experience.\r\n\r\nJust a kilometer from the mall, The Naini Retreat is situated on the picturesque Ayarpatta Slopes providing a breathtaking view of the Naini Lake at an altitude of 1995 meters. \r\n\r\nThe Himalayan resort re-awakens the pleasures of living- with a trek into the mountains, a golfing date at the regal hundred year old Raj Bhawan Golf Course, a special cultural evening featuring performances by traditional Kumaoni artists or a yacht ride at the highest sailing club in the world.','The Naini Retreat, Ayarpatta Slopes, Mallital ,Nainital-263001, Uttarakhand, India  ',42,NULL,24,'24-Hour Checkout','62','the-naini-retreat--2','2013-07-20 18:38:12','2013-07-20 18:38:12',NULL,NULL);

